SYNOPSIS
--------
RETRO-GAMES is a terminal-based collection of classic games written in C, using ncurses for the user interface. It includes implementations of Snake, Tetris, Pac-Man, Pong, Breakout, Chess, Minesweeper, and Sudoku.

FEATURES
--------
- Modular C codebase with GNU Autotools build system.
- Multiple classic games, each in its own module.
- Terminal-based UI using ncurses.
- Easily extensible for new games.

INSTALLATION
------------
To build and install RETRO-GAMES, use the standard GNU procedure:

  1. Unpack the source code:
	  $ tar xvf retro-games-x.y.tar.gz
	  $ cd retro-games-x.y

  2. Configure the package for your system:
	  $ ./configure [OPTIONS]

  3. Build and install:
	  $ make
	  $ make check      # optional: run tests
	  $ make install

USAGE
-----
Run the main program from the terminal:
	 $ retro-games

Follow the on-screen menu to select and play a game.

DEVELOPMENT
-----------
- Source code is in `src/` and `include/`.
- Each game has its own subdirectory under `src/games/` and `include/games/`.
- Documentation is in `doc/` (Texinfo format).
- Build system uses GNU Autotools (`configure.ac`, `Makefile.am`).

